Rule 1: Environment Management
- Use separate environment configurations for development, staging, and production
- Store sensitive data in environment variables
- Use .env files for local development
- Never commit sensitive data to version control

Rule 2: Database Deployment
- Always backup database before major changes
- Use migration scripts for schema changes
- Test migrations on staging environment first
- Monitor database performance in production

Rule 3: Smart Contract Deployment
- Deploy contracts to testnet first
- Verify contracts on blockchain explorers
- Update contract addresses in configuration
- Monitor contract events and transactions

Rule 4: Service Monitoring
- Implement health checks for all services
- Monitor API response times and error rates
- Set up alerts for critical failures
- Maintain comprehensive logging for debugging
